   abstract = {Outlines the nature of climate change related threats for the top 25% of Australia's bird taxa. Machine generated contents note: exposure of Australian birds to climate change / T. Stephen Garnett -- sensitivity of Australian birds to climate change / A. Justin Welbergen -- vulnerability of Australian birds to climate change / T. Stephen Garnett -- Conserving Australian bird populations in the face of climate change / T. Stephen Garnett -- Adaptation profiles for Australian birds that are both highly sensitive and highly exposed / Donald C. Franklin -- Brown Cuckoo-Dove -- Chestnut-quilled Rock-Pigeon -- Banded Fruit-Dove -- Wompoo Fruit-Dove -- White-rumped Swiftlet -- White-bellied Storm-Petrel -- Wedge-tailed Shearwater -- Little Shearwater -- Kermadec Petrel -- Herald Petrel -- Gould's Petrel -- White-necked Petrel -- Masked Booby -- Lord Howe Woodhen -- Beach Stone-curlew -- Australian Pied Oystercatcher -- Hooded Plover -- Painted Button-quail -- Black Noddy -- Lesser Noddy -- Grey Ternlet -- Sooty Tern -- Little Tern -- Fairy Tern -- Palm Cockatoo -- Red-tailed Black-Cockatoo -- Glossy Black-Cockatoo -- Double-eyed Fig-Parrot -- Eclectus Parrot -- Orange-bellied Parrot -- Western Ground Parrot -- Southern Boobook -- Noisy Pitta -- Rufous Scrub-bird -- Noisy Scrub-bird -- Spotted Catbird -- Western Bowerbird -- Southern Emu-wren -- Short-tailed Grasswren -- Black Grasswren -- Eastern Bristlebird -- Western Bristlebird -- Scrubtit -- Chestnut-rumped Heathwren -- Slender-billed Thornbill -- Brown Thornbill -- Forty-spotted Pardalote -- Yellow-tinted Honeyeater -- Black-eared Miner -- Chowchilla -- Western Whipbird -- Pied Currawong -- Black Currawong -- Frilled Monarch -- Yellow-breasted Boatbill -- Trumpet Manucode -- Scarlet Robin -- Northern Scrub-robin -- Horsfield's Bushlark.},
